# LeanOut Frontend & Design System Rules

You are editing a LeanOut UI component or page. The app has a deliberate, consistent visual identity — the "clean & energetic" orange design system. Every screen a user sees should feel native to this system. Consistency is a UX feature.

---

## Route group discipline — where pages live

| Page type | Route group | Why |
|---|---|---|
| Authenticated (has sidebar) | `src/app/(app)/` | Inherits `layout.tsx` which renders `<AppNav>` + `md:pl-60` content offset |
| Unauthenticated (login, register) | `src/app/(auth)/` | No sidebar, no nav |

**Never** create an authenticated page outside `(app)/` — it will render without the sidebar and break navigation. **Never** add auth checks to `(app)` pages directly — `proxy.ts` handles route protection globally.

---

## Design tokens — use these, never invent alternatives

All tokens are defined in `src/app/globals.css`. Reference them by class name or CSS variable. Do not hardcode color values.

### Colors — CSS variables

```css
/* Primary orange */
--color-primary: oklch(0.65 0.22 42)   /* ≈ #f97316 — DO NOT hardcode this value */

/* Sidebar */
--sidebar: oklch(0.13 0.01 260)        /* dark navy */
```

**Never** write `bg-orange-500`, `text-orange-400`, `#f97316`, or any ad-hoc orange value in a component. Always use the CSS variable or the utility classes below.

### Gradient utilities

```
.gradient-orange       → primary orange → deep orange  (buttons, section headers, hero areas)
.gradient-orange-soft  → pale orange tint              (result cards, selected/active states)
```

### Shadow utilities — replace ALL Tailwind shadow-* with these

```
.card-shadow     → standard card elevation
.card-shadow-md  → elevated card (modals, overlays, focused cards)
```

**Never** use `shadow-sm`, `shadow`, `shadow-md`, `shadow-lg`, or any Tailwind `shadow-*` class. They are not part of the design system and will look inconsistent.

### Typography utilities — for metric displays

```
.stat-number     → font-weight: 800, letter-spacing: -0.04em  (primary stats)
.stat-number-lg  → larger variant                              (hero numbers, dashboard callouts)
```

Use these for any prominent numeric display (calorie totals, macro grams, weight values, XP, streak count).

