## Component usage hierarchy

Before writing a new component or pulling in a new dependency, check in this order:

1. **Existing shadcn components** in `src/components/ui/` — Button, Card, Input, Badge, Progress, Dialog, Sheet, etc. Use these first.
2. **Existing LeanOut components** in `src/components/` — `AppNav`, `GamificationCard`, `CheckInCelebration`, `FoodLogReview`. Check if any of these can be composed or extended.
3. **New component** — only if neither of the above applies.
4. **New npm dependency** — requires explicit approval. Do not add UI libraries, animation libraries, or component kits without asking.

---

## Mobile-first layout requirements

LeanOut users are primarily on mobile (at the gym, in the kitchen). Every page and component must:

- **Work at 375px viewport width.** Test your layout mentally at this width before shipping.
- **Account for the bottom tab bar on mobile.** `<AppNav>` renders a bottom tab bar on small screens. Content near the bottom of the viewport must have enough padding to not be occluded by it. Use `pb-20` or `pb-24` on page root containers as needed.
- **Place primary actions in the bottom half of the viewport on mobile** where thumb reach is natural. Avoid top-of-screen-only CTAs for actions users take repeatedly (log food, submit check-in).
- **Use `md:` breakpoint** for desktop-specific layout shifts (the sidebar appears at `md:`, content is offset with `md:pl-60`).

---

## Page structure template

New `(app)` pages should follow this structure:

```tsx
// src/app/(app)/your-feature/page.tsx
export default function YourFeaturePage() {
  return (
    <div className="min-h-screen bg-background">
      {/* Page header */}
      <div className="gradient-orange px-4 pt-6 pb-8 md:px-8">
        <h1 className="text-2xl font-bold text-white">Page Title</h1>
        <p className="text-orange-100 text-sm mt-1">Supporting context</p>
      </div>

      {/* Content */}
      <div className="px-4 md:px-8 -mt-4 pb-24 space-y-4">
        {/* Cards use card-shadow, not shadow-md */}
        <div className="bg-card rounded-2xl p-4 card-shadow">
          ...
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  )
}
```

The `-mt-4` overlap between the gradient header and the card content is a deliberate visual pattern used across the app (dashboard, meal plan, food log). Preserve it on new pages.

---

## Data fetching in (app) pages

- Use `fetch` with `credentials: 'include'` or SWR for client-side fetching from API routes.
- Do not fetch from external APIs directly in client components — go through `src/app/api/**` routes which handle auth, validation, and secrets.
- Show a loading state immediately — never render an empty/broken layout while data loads. Use skeleton patterns consistent with existing pages.
- On API error, show an inline error state within the page — do not crash to an unhandled error boundary for recoverable errors (network failure, 4xx).

---

## Forms and interactions

- Use controlled components with `useState` for form state — no uncontrolled inputs or `ref`-based form reads in new code.
- Validate client-side before submitting — give immediate feedback on invalid fields (out-of-range scores, empty required fields) without waiting for a server round-trip.
- Disable submit buttons during in-flight requests. Show a loading indicator. Prevent double-submission.
- After a successful mutation, update local state optimistically or re-fetch — never require a page reload.

---

## Gamification UX — surface it, don't hide it

Gamification is a core engagement driver. When a user action awards XP or unlocks a badge:
- Use `<CheckInCelebration>` or an equivalent overlay — don't silently update the XP bar.
- The `POST /api/check-in` response includes `{ reward }` — always consume this and show the celebration if `reward.xpAwarded > 0` or `reward.newBadges.length > 0`.

---

## What NOT to do

- Do not use `shadow-*` Tailwind utilities anywhere. Use `.card-shadow` or `.card-shadow-md`.
- Do not hardcode `#f97316`, `orange-500`, or any color value — use CSS variables.
- Do not create pages outside the `(app)` or `(auth)` route groups.
- Do not add `useEffect` + `fetch` patterns where a direct server component or route handler fetch would work.
- Do not render sensitive data (full profile, scores, weight) in page titles, URL params, or anywhere outside the authenticated layout.
- Do not install new UI component libraries — extend shadcn or write a minimal component.
